{"build_type":"library","description":"Run one shell tool invocation in a forked child whose standard output is redirected into a pipe, and collect the child output bytes in the parent. callctx packs three handles: the shell library directory, the shell dispatch entry name, and a prebuilt argv array (shell path, shell path, request string, null). The child duplicates the pipe write end onto file descriptor one, closes both pipe ends it inherited, in-process loads the shell dispatch entry (which resolves and runs the named tool), then exits. The parent closes the write end, reads the pipe to end of stream into capbuf bounded by capcap, reaps the child, closes the read end, and returns the number of bytes collected.","module_name":"collect-forked-shell-process-output-bytes","package_name":"collect-forked-shell-process-output-bytes","function_definitions":{"collect-forked-shell-process-output-bytes":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"callctx","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"capbuf","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"capcap","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"negone","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":-1},{"instruction_type":